# core.autocrlf is true on Windows checkouts, which would rewrite these files to
# CRLF in the working tree. For helpbot/ that is not cosmetic:
#
# pack.txt is sent verbatim as the model's system message, and the provider's
# prefix cache only hits on an EXACT byte match. If a Windows checkout produced
# CRLF and CI produced LF, the two would deploy different packs, the cache would
# stop hitting, and every request would silently bill at roughly 120x the cached
# rate. `build_pack.py --check` would also fail spuriously against its own output.
#
# Pin the whole helpbot tree to LF so every machine and CI agree byte for byte.
helpbot/** text eol=lf
helpbot/pack/pack.txt text eol=lf
